metadata.name: SEL Setup without Addons
metadata.description:
Fully configured setup based on Tamtaro's recommended filters, sort orders, and Standard SEL described [here](https://github.com/Tam-Taro/SEL-Filtering-and-Sorting). Designed for those with debrid or usenet services, while seeking the highest quality results, minimal clutter, and complete coverage even when options are few. 

 * **Comes with no addons, so using this template will not affect your addons page** 
 * Standard SEL keeps around 15-20 results. Import Extended SEL Only template afterwards to keep more. Github has more SEL options to try out. 
 * **‚ìò For catalogs, check out Github for AIOMetadata configs.**
 * Review the Language filter. Add your main languages to Preferred Languages, keep rest the same. 
 * Some addons are included but disabled; just turn them on if you use them (eg. Torbox). 
 * This setup uses [Vidhin's regex](https://github.com/Vidhin05/Releases-Regex) to rank streams from reputable release groups. Big thx! ‚ò∫Ô∏è

metadata.name: Complete SEL Setup
metadata.description:
Fully configured setup based on Tamtaro's recommended filters, sort orders, and Standard SEL described on the [github](https://github.com/Tam-Taro/SEL-Filtering-and-Sorting). Designed for those with debrid or usenet services, while seeking the highest quality results, minimal clutter, and complete coverage even when options are few. 

 * Comes with addons and formatter. Use my other templates to keep your existing addons/formatter. 
 * Standard SEL keeps around 15-20 results. Import Extended SEL Only template afterwards to keep more. Github has more SEL options to try out. 
 * **‚ìò For catalogs, check out Github for AIOMetadata configs.**
 * Review the Language filter. Add your main languages to Preferred Languages, keep rest the same. 
 * Some addons are included but disabled; just turn them on if you use them (eg. Torbox). 
 * This setup uses [Vidhin's regex](https://github.com/Vidhin05/Releases-Regex) to rank streams from reputable release groups. Big thx! ‚ò∫Ô∏è

metadata.name: SEL Setup without Addons or Formatter
metadata.description:
Fully configured setup based on Tamtaro's recommended filters, sort orders, and Standard SEL described [here](https://github.com/Tam-Taro/SEL-Filtering-and-Sorting). Designed for those with debrid or usenet services, while seeking the highest quality results, minimal clutter, and complete coverage even when options are few. 

 * **Comes with no addons or formatter, so your existing addons page and formatter won't be affected** 
 * Standard SEL keeps around 15-20 results. Import Extended SEL Only template afterwards to keep more. Github has more SEL options to try out. 
 * **‚ìò For catalogs, check out Github for AIOMetadata configs.**
 * Review the Language filter. Add your main languages to Preferred Languages, keep rest the same. 
 * Some addons are included but disabled; just turn them on if you use them (eg. Torbox). 
 * This setup uses [Vidhin's regex](https://github.com/Vidhin05/Releases-Regex) to rank streams from reputable release groups. Big thx! ‚ò∫Ô∏è

metadata.description: This template has only the Standard SEL used in the Complete SEL Setup. It will import all Excluded + Included + Preferred Stream Expressions, so everything on Stream Expressions page except Ranked Stream Expressions. Read up on [Github](https://github.com/Tam-Taro/SEL-Filtering-and-Sorting) for more info & optional SELs to try. Nothing else will get overridden in your setup. To make use of the Preferred Stream Expressions, you will need to add Stream Expressions Matched into your Sort Order. The SEL template comes with multiple lines that smartly filter your results when necessary so that your final result page has a complete coverage of quality streams and minimal clutter. Around 15-20 streams should remain after filtering on average, depending on your source availability. Check out Extended SEL Only Template if you want to keep more.
